wfWcpLineTable.name: wfWcpLineTable
wfWcpLineTable.description: The line table contains line entries.

wfWcpLineEntry.name: wfWcpLineEntry
wfWcpLineEntry.description: The components of the instance ID of a line entry.

wfWcpLineDelete.name: wfWcpLineDelete
wfWcpLineDelete.description: Indicates whether the instance have been created or deleted.

wfWcpLineDisable.name: wfWcpLineDisable
wfWcpLineDisable.description: Indicates whether the instance have been enabled or disabled.

wfWcpLineEngineType.name: wfWcpLineEngineType
wfWcpLineEngineType.description: Indicates whether to use hardware or software compression

wfWcpLineSearchDepth.name: wfWcpLineSearchDepth
wfWcpLineSearchDepth.description: This attribute is only relevant for HW Compression VCs configured for CPC, 8K history. It indicates the Search Depth configured for this line. Increasing this attribute may allow the user to achieve better Compression ratios. This however could occur at the expense of throughput (i.e. you may get better compression ratios, but lower throughput). Note that this value may be set to 0, if the user wishes to run their Line in High Speed mode.

wfWcpLineFallbackCompressionMode.name: wfWcpLineFallbackCompressionMode
wfWcpLineFallbackCompressionMode.description: This attribute is only relevant for HW Compression VCs configured for CPC. It indicates what Compression Mode the user wants All VCs on a line to use, when any VC on that line is unable to register for HW Compression due to a lack of physical HW Context memory (Note that only HW CPC contexts can fail registration in this way).

wfWcpLineClientCompressorRingSize.name: wfWcpLineClientCompressorRingSize
wfWcpLineClientCompressorRingSize.description: Specifies the client compressor ring size for clients of this line. The default value is ZERO which will cause the hardware compression to assign the hard coded default value.

wfWcpLineClientDecompressorRingSize.name: wfWcpLineClientDecompressorRingSize
wfWcpLineClientDecompressorRingSize.description: Specifies the client decompressor ring size for clients of this line. The default value is ZERO which will cause the hardware compression to assign the hard coded default value.

wfWcpCircuitId.description: Indicates the circuit ID of this entry.

wfWcpCircuitCompressionMode.name: wfWcpCircuitCompressionMode
wfWcpCircuitCompressionMode.description: suitable when the line is relatively noisy.

wfWcpCircuitEngineType.name: wfWcpCircuitEngineType
wfWcpCircuitEngineType.description: Indicates whether to use hardware or software compression

wfWcpCircuitSearchDepth.name: wfWcpCircuitSearchDepth
wfWcpCircuitSearchDepth.description: This attribute is only relevant for HW Compression VCs configured for CPC, 8K history. It indicates the Search Depth configured for this circuit. Increasing this attribute may allow the user to achieve better Compression ratios. This however could occur at the expense of throughput (i.e. you may get better compression ratios, but lower throughput). Note that this value may be set to 0, if the user wishes to run this circuit in High Speed mode. Note that the default value of 256 is actually used to indicate that that this attribute should be inherited from wfWcpLineEntry MIB & is not a valid search depth value. Valid Search Depth values lie within the 1..255 range.

wfWcpVcRxRexmitNaks.description: Indicates the number of re-transmit Nak received.

wfWcpVcDataOutOfSeqs.name: wfWcpVcDataOutOfSeqs
wfWcpVcDataOutOfSeqs.description: Indicates the number of times that a data indication is out of sequence.

wfWcpVcRexmitOutOfSeqs.name: wfWcpVcRexmitOutOfSeqs
wfWcpVcRexmitOutOfSeqs.description: Indicates the number of times that a re-transmit Ack is out of sequence.

wfWcpVcRexmitTimeouts.name: wfWcpVcRexmitTimeouts
wfWcpVcRexmitTimeouts.description: Indicates the number of re-transmit timeout.

wfWcpVcExceededKs.name: wfWcpVcExceededKs
wfWcpVcExceededKs.description: Indicates the number of times that K is exceeded.

wfWcpVcInvalidOpCodes.name: wfWcpVcInvalidOpCodes

wfWcpVcSearchDepth.description: This attribute is only relevant for HW Compression VCs configured for CPC, 8K history. It indicates the Search Depth configured for this VC. Increasing this attribute may allow the user to achieve better Compression ratios. This however could occur at the expense of throughput (i.e. you may get better compression ratios, but lower throughput). Note that this value may be 0, if the user wishes to run their VC in High Speed Mode.

wfHwCompTable.name: wfHwCompTable
wfHwCompTable.description: The HW Compression Table contains compression entries.

wfHwCompEntry.name: wfHwCompEntry
wfHwCompEntry.description: Slot number used as instance identifier.

wfHwCompSlot.name: wfHwCompSlot
wfHwCompSlot.description: Slot number -- gotten from the instance ID.

wfHwCompModule.name: wfHwCompModule
wfHwCompModule.description: Module # -- gotten from the instance ID.

wfHwCompEngineNumber.name: wfHwCompEngineNumber
wfHwCompEngineNumber.description: Compression Engine #. Gotten from the instance ID.

wfHwCompCompressionHistoryTotal.name: wfHwCompCompressionHistoryTotal
wfHwCompCompressionHistoryTotal.description: The amount of memory allocated for Compression History.

wfHwCompCompressionHashTblSize.name: wfHwCompCompressionHashTblSize
wfHwCompCompressionHashTblSize.description: The amount of memory allocated for Compression Hash Tables. These Hash Tables are used to do lookups in Compression History memory.

wfHwCompDecompressionHistoryTotal.name: wfHwCompDecompressionHistoryTotal
wfHwCompDecompressionHistoryTotal.description: The amount of memory allocated for Decompression History.

wfHwComp8kContextsTotal.name: wfHwComp8kContextsTotal
wfHwComp8kContextsTotal.description: This indicates the maximum number of 8KB Context Control Blocks (CCBs) (i.e. VC's) we can support with this memory configuration. This is assuming ALL VC's using Variable Search Depth Mode, 8KB history size. This equals wfHwCompCompressionHistoryTotal divided by 8KB.

wfHwComp32kContextsTotal.name: wfHwComp32kContextsTotal
wfHwComp32kContextsTotal.description: This indicates the maximum number of 32KB Context Control Blocks (CCBs) (i.e. VC's) we can support with this memory configuration. This is assuming ALL VC's using High Speed, Single Search Mode, 32KB history size. This equals wfHwCompCompressionHistoryTotal divided by 32KB.

wfHwComp8kCpcContextsInUse.name: wfHwComp8kCpcContextsInUse
wfHwComp8kCpcContextsInUse.description: This indicates the current number of 8KB CPC (Continuous Packet Compression) Mode VC's using Hardware Compression services.

wfHwComp8kPpcContextsInUse.name: wfHwComp8kPpcContextsInUse
wfHwComp8kPpcContextsInUse.description: This indicates the number of PPC (Per Packet Compression) Mode VC's allocated for HW Compression. This value ALWAYS equates to 1, as 1 PPC Context is ALWAYS reserved as a resource for any VC doing HW Compression to use. All VC's configured to run in PPC Mode share this context. This context is also used when a VC enters Transient PPC Compression Mode, which occurs when frames are dropped or errors occur on the physical link.

wfHwComp32kContextsInUse.name: wfHwComp32kContextsInUse
wfHwComp32kContextsInUse.description: This indicates the current number of 32KB Context Control Blocks (CCBs) (i.e. VC's) using Hardware Compression services.

wfHwComp8kContextsAvailable.name: wfHwComp8kContextsAvailable
wfHwComp8kContextsAvailable.description: This indicates the number of 'usable' 8k Context Control Blocks available. Note that this will get reduced (by 4) when a user configures a VC for 32KB History Size (i.e. High Speed, Single Search Mode).

wfHwComp32kContextsAvailable.name: wfHwComp32kContextsAvailable
wfHwComp32kContextsAvailable.description: This indicates the number of 'usable' 32k Context Control Blocks available. This means that this/these number of pages of Compression Memory currently have NO Context Control Block (i.e.VC) associated with them.

wfHwCompCpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompCpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompCpcContextsRegistered.description: This indicates the number of VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Continuous Packet Compression (CPC) mode. Anytime a VC/Context successfully registers with HW Compression using this mode, a HW context has been dedicated to that VC.

wfHwCompPpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompPpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompPpcContextsRegistered.description: This indicates the number of VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Packet by Packet Compression (PPC) mode. All VCs/Contexts which register using PPC mode, share 1 HW Context which has been dedicated for use by PPC Vcs.

wfHwCompCompressionTotalRingSize.name: wfHwCompCompressionTotalRingSize
wfHwCompCompressionTotalRingSize.description: This indicates the total number of Descriptor ring entries available for HW Compression.

wfHwCompDecompressionTotalRingSize.name: wfHwCompDecompressionTotalRingSize
wfHwCompDecompressionTotalRingSize.description: This indicates the total number of Descriptor ring entries available for HW Decompression.

wfHwCompCompressionCurrentQueued.name: wfHwCompCompressionCurrentQueued
wfHwCompCompressionCurrentQueued.description: This is a snapshot of the current number of entries outstanding on the HW Compression Ring.

wfHwCompDecompressionCurrentQueued.name: wfHwCompDecompressionCurrentQueued
wfHwCompDecompressionCurrentQueued.description: This is a snapshot of the current number of entries outstanding on the HW Decompression Ring.

wfHwCompCompressionQHiWatermark.name: wfHwCompCompressionQHiWatermark
wfHwCompCompressionQHiWatermark.description: This indicates the largest number of frames ever outstanding on the HW Compression Ring since this Compression Engine started providing HW Compression services.

wfHwCompDecompressionQHiWatermark.name: wfHwCompDecompressionQHiWatermark
wfHwCompDecompressionQHiWatermark.description: This indicates the largest number of frames ever outstanding on the HW Decompression Ring since this Compression Engine started providing HW Compression services.

wfHwCompTxExpandedPkts.name: wfHwCompTxExpandedPkts
wfHwCompTxExpandedPkts.description: The # of pkts given to the Compressor which actually expanded instead of compressing.

wfHwCompTxNonCompressedPkts.name: wfHwCompTxNonCompressedPkts
wfHwCompTxNonCompressedPkts.description: This indicates a temporary Buffer Starvation condition. When we cannot get a buffer to Compress into, this stat gets incremented & the original UnCompressed frame is sent.

wfHwCompRxNonCompressedPkts.name: wfHwCompRxNonCompressedPkts
wfHwCompRxNonCompressedPkts.description: The # of pkts received across the link which happened to come across the link uncompressed. This can be either because the pkt was an Expanded pkt at the remote end or for some reason the sending device could not compress this particular pkt due to resource issues.

wfHwCompRxDroppedPkts.name: wfHwCompRxDroppedPkts
wfHwCompRxDroppedPkts.description: This indicates a temporary Buffer Starvation condition. When we cannot get a buffer to Decompress into, this stat gets incremented & the received Compressed data frame is run through the Decompressor in order to update the Decompressors histories and then dropped.

wfHwCompRxLcbMismatches.name: wfHwCompRxLcbMismatches
wfHwCompRxLcbMismatches.description: This indicates a frame was dropped between the remote end and this end. Line errors such as CRC Errors cause this. Buffer starvation in this router can also cause this.

wfHwCompCompressionRingOverflows.name: wfHwCompCompressionRingOverflows
wfHwCompCompressionRingOverflows.description: Number of frames dropped due to Compression Descriptor Ring full condition.

wfHwCompDecompressionRingOverflows.name: wfHwCompDecompressionRingOverflows
wfHwCompDecompressionRingOverflows.description: Number of frames dropped due to Decompression Descriptor Ring full condition.

wfHwCompCompressionErrors.name: wfHwCompCompressionErrors
wfHwCompCompressionErrors.description: Indicates the total # of Compression Errors detected on this module.

wfHwCompDecompressionErrors.name: wfHwCompDecompressionErrors
wfHwCompDecompressionErrors.description: Indicates the total # of Decompression Errors detected on this module.

wfHwCompCompressionSrcPktLenErrors.name: wfHwCompCompressionSrcPktLenErrors
wfHwCompCompressionSrcPktLenErrors.description: A zero length source packet was received by the Compressor or Decompressor.

wfHwCompCompressionCcbFormatErrors.name: wfHwCompCompressionCcbFormatErrors
wfHwCompCompressionCcbFormatErrors.description: The format of the specified Context Control Block (CCB) was detected to be in error.

wfHwCompCompressionDescFormatErrors.name: wfHwCompCompressionDescFormatErrors
wfHwCompCompressionDescFormatErrors.description: The format of the current descriptor is in error.

wfHwCompCompressionInternalErrors.name: wfHwCompCompressionInternalErrors
wfHwCompCompressionInternalErrors.description: The Compressor or Decompressor took an internal error when processing this descriptor.

wfHwCompDecompressionSrcPktLenErrors.name: wfHwCompDecompressionSrcPktLenErrors
wfHwCompDecompressionSrcPktLenErrors.description: A zero length source packet was received by the Compressor or Decompressor.

wfHwCompDecompressionCcbFormatErrors.name: wfHwCompDecompressionCcbFormatErrors
wfHwCompDecompressionCcbFormatErrors.description: The format of the specified Context Control Block (CCB) was detected to be in error.

wfHwCompDecompressionDescFormatErrors.name: wfHwCompDecompressionDescFormatErrors
wfHwCompDecompressionDescFormatErrors.description: The format of the current descriptor is in error.

wfHwCompDecompressionInternalErrors.name: wfHwCompDecompressionInternalErrors
wfHwCompDecompressionInternalErrors.description: The Compressor or Decompressor took an internal error when processing this descriptor.

wfHwCompChipType.name: wfHwCompChipType
wfHwCompChipType.description: Compression Chip Type: MAGNALINK or ITCS

wfHwCompMsaCpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompMsaCpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompMsaCpcContextsRegistered.description: The number of MSA VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Continuous Packet Compression (CPC) mode. Anytime an MSA VC/Context successfully registers with HW Compression using this mode, a HW context has been dedicated to that VC.

wfHwCompMsaPpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompMsaPpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompMsaPpcContextsRegistered.description: The number of MSA VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Packet by Packet Compression (PPC) mode. All MSA VCs/Contexts which register using PPC mode, share 1 HW Context which has been dedicated for use by PPC Vcs.

wfHwCompMsa8KContextsGuaranteed.name: wfHwCompMsa8KContextsGuaranteed
wfHwCompMsa8KContextsGuaranteed.description: The number of 8K MSA contexts reserved with a particular memory carving. Calculated as number of pages guaranteed for MSA times 4, where 4 is the maximum number of 8K MSA contexts per page.

wfHwCompStacContextsTotal.name: wfHwCompStacContextsTotal
wfHwCompStacContextsTotal.description: The maximum number of STAC CCBs that can be supported for a particular memory carving.

wfHwCompStacCpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompStacCpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompStacCpcContextsRegistered.description: This indicates the number of STAC VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Continuous Packet Compression (CPC) mode. Anytime a STAC VC/Context successfully registers with HW Compression using this mode, a HW context has been dedicated to that VC.

wfHwCompStacPpcContextsRegistered.name: wfHwCompStacPpcContextsRegistered
wfHwCompStacPpcContextsRegistered.description: The number of STAC VC's which have registered for HW Compression and are using Packet by Packet Compression (PPC) mode. All STAC VCs/Contexts which register using PPC mode, share 1 HW Context which has been dedicated for use by PPC Vcs.

wfHwCompStacPpcContextsInUse.name: wfHwCompStacPpcContextsInUse
wfHwCompStacPpcContextsInUse.description: The number of STAC contexts allocated for PPC. Equals 1 if STAC is enabled, 0 if it is disabled.

wfHwCompStacContextsAvailable.name: wfHwCompStacContextsAvailable
wfHwCompStacContextsAvailable.description: The number of 'usable' STAC context control blocks available.

wfHwCompStacContextsGuaranteed.name: wfHwCompStacContextsGuaranteed
wfHwCompStacContextsGuaranteed.description: The number of STAC contexts reserved with a particular memory carving. Calculated as number of pages guaranteed for STAC times 8, where 8 is the maximum number of STAC contexts per page.

wfHwCompMsaCompressedPkts.name: wfHwCompMsaCompressedPkts
wfHwCompMsaCompressedPkts.description: The # of pkts successfully compressed using MSA compression algorithm.

wfHwCompStacDecompressedPkts.description: The # of pkts successfully decompressed using STAC compression algorithm.

wfHwCompMsaTxExpandedPkts.description: The # of pkts given to the Compressor which actually expanded instead of compressing using MSA compression algorithm.

wfHwCompStacTxExpandedPkts.description: The # of pkts given to the Compressor which actually expanded instead of compressing using STAC compression algorithm.

wfHwCompMsaTxNonCompressedPkts.name: wfHwCompMsaTxNonCompressedPkts
wfHwCompMsaTxNonCompressedPkts.description: This indicates a temporary Buffer Starvation condition. When we cannot get a buffer to Compress into, this stat gets incremented & the original UnCompressed frame is sent.

wfHwCompStacTxNonCompressedPkts.description: This indicates a temporary Buffer Starvation condition. When we cannot get a buffer to Compress into, this stat gets incremented & the original UnCompressed frame is sent.

wfHwCompMsaRxNonCompressedPkts.name: wfHwCompMsaRxNonCompressedPkts
